The four fragments in the fasta file here are the copies of the Rcc1 fragments from the two oldest duplicates (Figure 5, branch 2) in the phylogeny, in two species. 
Their names (mush/shifted) correspond to the syntenic conserved genes at the locus, visible in Figure 5: mushroom bodies tiny (mbt, mush) and shifted. 
They can be found in the genome annotations using these syntenic genes. 



